nLibrary coordinates should be provided in the prompt in the format `group:artifact:version`. If you are not sure what the coordinates are, ask the user.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Workflow\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Reproduce the failure:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` from repository root.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Capture the missing metadata from the error message:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Locate any `Missing*RegistrationError` (e.g. `MissingReflectionRegistrationError`, `MissingResourceRegistrationError`, or any other variant).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type into the corresponding section of the reachability-metadata.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Choose the target file and insert the entry:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Keep valid JSON and avoid duplicating an existing equivalent entry. If the type already exists but a method or field is missing, add only that method or field.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. Add the missing `condition` field:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Infer it from the error stack trace.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Set the `condition` field to `{ \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"typeReached\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<class>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" }`, where `<class>` is the first class on the stack trace whose package shares the leading namespace with the tested library's package.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Package overlap can be partial, full package equality is not required.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Example: tested library's group `org.hibernate.orm...` and the class from a stack trace `org.hibernate.resource...` is a valid match.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n5. Verify and iterate:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` again.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - If another missing entry appears, repeat from step 2.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - Finish only when the test run succeeds.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Error Patterns\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nUse this reference when deriving the missing entry and condition.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Missing Registration Entry Pattern\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nExample error shape:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator()'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n...\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nadd the following to the 'reflection' section of reachability-metadata.json:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"methods\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [{ \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<init>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"parameterTypes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [] }]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n...\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nat org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder.instantiateGeneratorViaDefaultConstructor(...)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nat org.hibernate.resource.beans.internal.Helper$2.produceBeanInstance(...)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Condition Inference\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nFor missing type `org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator`, a valid condition class is:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nReason: both share the leading namespace `org.hibernate`, which is sufficient for this workflow.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Environment Troubleshooting\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- If they are not set to GraalVM, ask the user to provide the correct GraalVM distribution path and retry.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n8:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent_message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"The required GraalVM is available and `native-image --version` matches the specified `25.0.2` build. Next I’m running the exact failing Gradle test with `GRAALVM_HOME` and `JAVA_HOME` pinned to that distribution, then I’ll patch the metadata based on the first missing-registration error and iterate until the test passes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n9:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.started\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_4\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"todo_list\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"items\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Reproduce `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.springframework.data:spring-data-jpa:2.7.18` with the required GraalVM environment\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":false},{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Update the relevant `reachability-metadata.json` entries based on missing-registration errors\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":false},{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Verify the Gradle test passes with the same GraalVM distribution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\